⏺ Privacy Policy for Roofy (Roof Analyzer)

  Last Updated: March 2, 2026

  ---
  Introduction

  Roofy ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to
  protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains
  how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your
  information when you use our mobile application (the
  "App"). Please read this privacy policy carefully. If
  you do not agree with the terms of this privacy
  policy, please do not access the App.

  ---
  1. Information We Collect

  1.1 Information You Provide

  Account Information
  - Email address (if you create an account)
  - Name and contact information (if provided)
  - Subscription and payment information (processed by
  Apple)

  User-Generated Content
  - Property addresses you search
  - Custom measurements and annotations
  - Project names and organization
  - Saved analysis data

  1.2 Automatically Collected Information

  Device Information
  - Device type and model
  - Operating system version
  - Unique device identifiers
  - App version and build number

  Usage Information
  - Features used within the App
  - Analysis history and frequency
  - App performance data
  - Crash reports and error logs

  Location Information
  - Approximate location (for address autocomplete
  suggestions)
  - We do NOT track your precise GPS location
  continuously
  - Location data is only used when you search for an
  address

  1.3 Information from Third Parties

  Google Maps Platform
  - Satellite imagery
  - Geocoding data
  - Place autocomplete suggestions
  - Solar irradiance data (via Google Solar API)

  Payment Processing
  - Subscription status and purchase history (via Apple
  App Store and RevenueCat)
  - We do NOT store your payment card information

  ---
  2. How We Use Your Information

  We use the information we collect to:

  2.1 Provide and Maintain the App

  - Process and fulfill your roof analysis requests
  - Display satellite imagery and solar data
  - Generate PDF reports
  - Save your analysis history
  - Sync data across your devices

  2.2 Improve User Experience

  - Analyze usage patterns to improve features
  - Fix bugs and technical issues
  - Develop new features based on user needs
  - Optimize app performance

  2.3 Communicate with You

  - Send important app updates and notifications
  - Respond to your support requests
  - Provide subscription information
  - Send promotional messages (with your consent)

  2.4 Process Subscriptions

  - Manage your subscription status
  - Process subscription renewals
  - Provide access to premium features
  - Track usage limits

  2.5 Legal and Security

  - Comply with legal obligations
  - Prevent fraud and abuse
  - Enforce our Terms of Service
  - Protect our rights and property

  ---
  3. Data Storage and Security

  3.1 Local Storage

  - Analysis data is stored locally on your device
  - We use iOS secure storage mechanisms
  - Data persists until you delete the app or clear it
  manually

  3.2 Cloud Storage

  - Subscription status is synced via Apple and
  RevenueCat
  - No personal analysis data is stored on our servers
  - We do not maintain a central database of your
  analyses

  3.3 Security Measures

  - Industry-standard encryption for data transmission
  (HTTPS/TLS)
  - Secure API communication with Google Maps Platform
  - No storage of payment card information
  - Regular security updates and patches

  3.4 Data Retention

  - Analysis data: Stored locally until you delete it
  - Account data: Retained while your subscription is
  active
  - Usage logs: Retained for 90 days
  - Crash reports: Retained for 12 months

  ---
  4. Third-Party Services

  We use the following third-party services that may
  collect information:

  4.1 Google Maps Platform

  - Purpose: Satellite imagery, geocoding, solar data
  - Data Shared: Search addresses, coordinates
  - Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

  4.2 Apple App Store & RevenueCat

  - Purpose: Subscription management and payment
  processing
  - Data Shared: Purchase information, subscription
  status
  - Privacy Policies:
    - Apple: https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/
    - RevenueCat: https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy/

  4.3 Expo (Development Platform)

  - Purpose: App performance monitoring
  - Data Shared: Crash reports, error logs
  - Privacy Policy: https://expo.dev/privacy

  ---
  5. Data Sharing and Disclosure

  5.1 We Do NOT Sell Your Data

  We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal
  information to third parties.

  5.2 Service Providers

  We may share information with service providers who
  help us operate the App:
  - Cloud infrastructure providers
  - Analytics services
  - Customer support tools

  These providers are contractually obligated to protect
   your information.

  5.3 Legal Requirements

  We may disclose your information if required by law or
   to:
  - Comply with legal process (subpoena, court order)
  - Protect our rights and property
  - Prevent illegal activity
  - Ensure user safety

  5.4 Business Transfers

  If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale
  of assets, your information may be transferred. We
  will notify you of any such change.

  ---
  6. Your Rights and Choices

  6.1 Access and Update

  - View your saved analyses within the App
  - Edit or delete any analysis
  - Update your account information

  6.2 Delete Your Data

  - Clear all analyses: Settings → Clear All Data
  - Delete the App to remove all local data
  - Contact us to request account deletion

  6.3 Location Permissions

  - Control location access in iOS Settings → Roofy
  - You can revoke location permission at any time
  - The App will still work but address autocomplete may
   be limited

  6.4 Marketing Communications

  - Opt out of promotional messages
  - Contact us at support@roofyapp.com

  6.5 Do Not Track

  We do not respond to Do Not Track signals as there is
  no industry standard for compliance.

  ---
  7. Children's Privacy

  The App is not intended for children under 13 years of
   age. We do not knowingly collect personal information
   from children under 13. If you are a parent or
  guardian and believe your child has provided us with
  personal information, please contact us immediately,
  and we will delete such information.

  ---
  8. International Users

  8.1 Data Processing

  Your information may be processed in the United States
   and other countries where our service providers
  operate.

  8.2 GDPR Rights (European Users)

  If you are in the European Economic Area (EEA), you
  have additional rights:
  - Right to Access: Request a copy of your data
  - Right to Rectification: Correct inaccurate data
  - Right to Erasure: Request deletion of your data
  - Right to Restrict Processing: Limit how we use your
  data
  - Right to Data Portability: Receive your data in a
  portable format
  - Right to Object: Object to processing of your data
  - Right to Withdraw Consent: Withdraw consent at any
  time

  To exercise these rights, contact us at
  privacy@roofyapp.com.

  8.3 CCPA Rights (California Users)

  If you are a California resident, you have the right
  to:
  - Know what personal information is collected
  - Know if personal information is sold or shared
  - Opt-out of sale of personal information (we do not
  sell data)
  - Request deletion of personal information
  - Non-discrimination for exercising your rights

